arl of Vermandois Hugh de Catte Hugh de Catte于1489年出生时，他的父亲Hugh Catlett DeCatte20岁，母亲Mary De Catte20岁。他于1508年与Mary Williams在英国英格兰肯特希廷波恩结婚。他们至少是1个儿子的父母。他去世于1520年享年31岁。"},"hr":{"1489–1520":"1489.–1520.","1487–Male":"1487–preminuo","1494–1525":"1494–1525","1509–1567":"1509–1567","1469–1499":"1469–1499.","1469–1500":"1469–1500.","1494":"1494","about 1509":"oko 1509.","1525":"1525","1469":"1469","1567":"1567","1489":"1489.","1500":"1500.","1499":"1499.","1520":"1520.","1487":"1487","1486":"1486.","1509":"1509","1508":"1508.","Leicestershire, England, United Kingdom":"Leicestershire, Engleska, United Kingdom","Sittingbourne, Kent, England, United Kingdom":"Sittingbourne, Kent, Engleska, United Kingdom"},"cs":{"1489–1520":"1489–1520","1487–Male":"1487–Zesnulý","1494–1525":"1494–1525","1509–1567":"1509–1567","1469–1499":"1469–1499","1469–1500":"1469–1500","1494":"1494","about 1509":"okolo 1509","1525":"1525","1469":"1469","1567":"1567","1489":"1489","1500":"1500","1499":"1499","1520":"1520","1487":"1487","1486":"1486","1509":"1509","1508":"1508","Leicestershire, England, United Kingdom":"Leicestershire, Anglie, United Kingdom","Sittingbourne, Kent, England, United Kingdom":"Sittingbourne, Kent, Anglie, United Kingdom"},"da":{"1489–1520":"1489–1520","1487–Male":"1487–Afdød","1494–1525":"1494–1525","1509–1567":"1509–1567","1469–1499":"1469–1499","1469–1500":"1469–1500","1494":"1494","about 1509":"omkring 1509","1525":"1525","1469":"1469","1567":"1567","1489":"1489","1500":"1500","1499":"1499","1520":"1520","1487":"1487","1486":"1486","1509":"1509","1508":"1508","Leicestershire, England, United Kingdom":"Leicestershire, England, United Kingdom","Sittingbourne, Kent, England, United Kingdom":"Sittingbourne, Kent, England, United Kingdom"},"nl":{"1489–1520":"1489–1520","1487–Male":"1487–Overleden","1494–1525":"1494–1525","1509–1567":"1509–1567","1469–1499":"1469–1499","1469–1500":"1469–1500","1494":"1494","about 1509":"circa 1509","1525":"1525","1469":"1469","1567":"1567","1489":"1489","1500":"1500","1499":"1499","1520":"1520","1487":"1487","1486":"1486","1509":"1509","1508":"1508","Leicestershire, England, United Kingdom":"Leicestershire, Engeland, Verenigd Koninkrijk","Sittingbourne, Kent, England, United Kingdom":"Sittingbourne, Kent, Engeland, Verenigd Koninkrijk"},"en":{"1489–1520":"1489–1520","1487–Male":"1487–Deceased","1494–1525":"1494–1525","1509–1567":"1509–1567","1469–1499":"1469–1499","1469–1500":"1469–1500","1494":"1494","about 1509":"about 1509","1525":"1525","1469":"1469","1567":"1567","1489":"1489","1500":"1500","1499":"1499","1520":"1520","1487":"1487","1486":"1486","1509":"1509","1508":"1508","Leicestershire, England, United Kingdom":"Leicestershire, England, United Kingdom","Sittingbourne, Kent, England, United Kingdom":"Sittingbourne, Kent, England, United Kingdom","nameMeanings":[{"name":"de","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  Indian Dilip, Anirban, Gopal, Alok, Anindya, Arunava, Asit, Asok, Dibyendu, Goutam, Indra, Indranil.","Indian: variant of   Dey  ."],"variants":[{"name":"Dey","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  Indian Ashit, Indu, Naina, Partha, Soumya, Ajit, Anjan, Anjana, Anup, Arjun, Arun, Ashim.","English, Scottish, and Welsh: variant of   Day  .","German: topographic name from a field name in North Rhine-Westphalia, denoting a sizeable piece of land, from Middle Low German <i>dē</i> ‘thigh’ (referring to the shape of the property)."]}]},{"name":"Catte","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["English: variant of   Catt  , with genitival or post-medieval excrescent <i>-s</i>. This surname is now rare in Britain.","Probably an Americanized form of German and Jewish (Ashkenazic)   Katz  , Dutch   Kats  , or German <b>Götz</b> (see   Goetz  )."],"variants":[{"name":"Catt","meanings":["English (Sussex and Kent): nickname from Middle English <i>c(h)at</i> ‘cat’ (Old English <i>catt</i>, Norman and Picard Old French <i>cat</i>, Parisian Old French <i>chat</i>). The word is found in similar forms in most European languages from very early times (e.g. Gaelic <i>cath</i>, Old Slavic <i>kotъ</i>). Domestic cats were unknown in Europe in classical times, when weasels fulfilled many of their functions, for example in hunting rodents. They seem to have come from Egypt, where they were regarded as sacred animals.","English: occasionally, perhaps from an unrecorded Middle English female personal name <i>Cat</i>, a pet form of <i>Catelin</i> ‘Catherine’. See   Catlin  . Alternatively, perhaps from an unrecorded Middle English personal name <i>Cat(te)</i> or <i>Chat(te)</i>, a survival of Old <i>C(e)atta</i>, which is well attested in placenames.","Americanized form of North German   Katt  ."]}]},{"name":"Hugh","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["From an Old French name, <i>Hugues</i>, <i>Hugo</i>, of Germanic (Frankish) origin, derived from <i>hug</i> ‘heart, mind, spirit’. It was originally a short form of various compound names containing this element. This was borne by the aristocracy of medieval France, adopted by the Normans, and introduced by them to Britain. It was consistently one of the most popular boys' names in the Middle Ages in England, but fell out of favour in the 16th century until it was revived in the 20th century. Little Hugh of Lincoln was a child supposed in the Middle Ages to have been murdered by Jews in about  1255 , a legend responsible for several outbursts of anti-Semitism at various times. The story is referred to by  Chaucer  in The Prioress's Tale. He is not to be confused with  St Hugh of Lincoln  (  1140–1200 ), bishop of Lincoln (  1186–1200 ), who was noted for his charity and good works, his piety, and his defence of the Church against the State. Since the later Middle Ages <i>Hugh</i> has also been used as an Anglicized form of the Gaelic name Aodh ."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"When Earl of Vermandois Hugh de Catte Hugh de Catte was born in 1489, his father, Hugh Catlett DeCatte, was 20 and his mother, Mary De Catte, was 20. He married Mary Williams in 1508, in Sittingbourne, Kent, England, United Kingdom. They were the parents of at least 1 son. He died in 1520, at the age of 31."},"et":{"1489–1520":"1489–1520","1487–Male":"1487–Surnud","1494–1525":"1494–1525","1509–1567":"1509–1567","1469–1499":"1469–1499","1469–1500":"1469–1500","1494":"1494","about 1509":"umbes 1509","1525":"1525","1469":"1469","1567":"1567","1489":"1489","1500":"1500","1499":"1499","1520":"1520","1487":"1487","1486":"1486","1509":"1509","1508":"1508","Leicestershire, England, United Kingdom":"Leicestershire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Sittingbourne, Kent, England, United Kingdom":"Sittingbourne, Kent, Inglismaa, United Kingdom"},"fi":{"1489–1520":"1489–1520","1487–Male":"1487–Kuollut","1494–1525":"1494–1525","1509–1567":"1509–1567","1469–1499":"1469–1499","1469–1500":"1469–1500","1494":"1494","about 1509":"noin 1509","1525":"1525","1469":"1469","1567":"1567","1489":"1489","1500":"1500","1499":"1499","1520":"1520","1487":"1487","1486":"1486","1509":"1509","1508":"1508","Leicestershire, England, United Kingdom":"Leicestershire, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","Sittingbourne, Kent, England, United Kingdom":"Sittingbourne, Kent, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta"},"fr":{"1489–1520":"1489–1520","1487–Male":"1487–Décédé","1494–1525":"1494–1525","1509–1567":"1509–1567","1469–1499":"1469–1499","1469–1500":"1469–1500","1494":"1494","about 1509":"environ 1509","1525":"1525","1469":"1469","1567":"1567","1489":"1489","1500":"1500","1499":"1499","1520":"1520","1487":"1487","1486":"1486","1509":"1509","1508":"1508","Leicestershire, England, United Kingdom":"Leicestershire, Angleterre, Royaume-Uni","Sittingbourne, Kent, England, United Kingdom":"Sittingbourne, Kent, Angleterre, Roy